    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                The data below represents the times (in seconds) recorded in the heats of a <m>100 \textbf{ m}</m> race during an athletics event:
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>14.5, 13.7, 14.8, 15.3, 15.1, 14.2, 14.9, 12.6, 11.9, 13.1, 12.3, 14.7, 14.1, 15.0,</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>14.3, 15.2, 11.7, 12.9, 13.5, 15.4, 12.8, 12.1, 14.4, 13.2, 14.6, 11.6, 12.7, 15.5</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>14.0, 14.9, 13.9, 12.0, 13.8, 15.2, 13.3</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Create a frequency distribution table using class intervals:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><m>11.5 - 11.9</m></li>
                                <li><m>12.0 - 12.4</m></li>
                                <li><m>12.5 - 12.9</m></li>
                                <li><m>13.0 - 13.4</m></li>
                                <li><m>13.5 - 13.9</m></li>
                                <li><m>14.0 - 14.4</m></li>
                                <li><m>14.5 - 14.9</m></li>
                                <li><m>15.0 - 15.4</m></li>
                                <li><m>15.5 - 15.9</m></li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Determine the modal class
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Estimate  median based on the frequency table.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the mean based on the frequency table.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            To create a frequency distribution table We need to count how many values fall into each class interval.
                        </p>
                        <table>
                            <title></title>
                            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                                <row halign="left" header="yes">
                                    <cell>Class Interval (seconds)</cell>
                                    <cell>Midpoint(x)</cell>
                                    <cell>Frequency(f)</cell>
                                    <cell>Cumulative frequency(CF)</cell>
                                    <cell>fx</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>11.5 - 11.9</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>11.7</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>23.4</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>12.0 - 12.4</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>12.2</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>36.6</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>12.5 - 12.9</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>12.7</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>38.1</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>13.0 - 13.4</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>13.2</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>4</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>12</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>52.8</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>13.5 - 13.9</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>13.7</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>4</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>16</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>54.8</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>14.0 - 14.4</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>14.2</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>21</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>71.0</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>14.5 - 14.9</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>14.7</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>26</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>73.5</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>15.0 - 15.4</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>15.2</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>4</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>30</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>60.8</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>15.5 - 15.9</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>15.7</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>1</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>31</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>15.7</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>\textbf{Total (∑)}</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>123.3</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>31</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>31</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>426.7</m></cell>
                                </row>
                            </tabular>
                        </table>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The modal class is the class interval with the highest frequency.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            From the table, The highest frequency is <m>5</m>, which appears in two class intervals: <m>14.0 - 14.4</m> and <m>14.5 - 14.9</m>.


                        </p>
                        <p>
                            So, the modal class are  <m>14.0 - 14.4</m> and <m>14.5 - 14.9</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Therefore, distribution is bimodal,
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Total frequency (∑f) = <m>31</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Median position is <m>\frac{31}{2}</m> = <m>15.5</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The median class is the first class where CF exceeds <m>15.5</m>, which is <m>13.5 - 13.9</m>.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Using the median formula:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \textbf{Median} = \amp  \textbf{L} + (\frac{\frac{n}{2} - \textbf{CF}}{\textbf{F}})\times \textbf{C}</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Where;
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        L = <m>13.5</m> (lower boundary of median class)
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        <m>\frac{n}{2}</m> = <m>15.5</m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        CF = <m>12</m> (cumulative frequency before the median class)
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        F = <m>4</m>(frequency of the median class)
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        C = <m>0.5</m> class width
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \textbf{Median} = \amp  13.5 + (\frac{15.5 - 12}{4})\times 0.5</mrow>
                                <mrow> =  \amp 13.5 + (\frac{3.5}{4}\times 0.5)</mrow>
                                <mrow> =  \amp 13.5 + 0.4375</mrow>
                                <mrow> =  \amp 13.94</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Therefore, <m>13.94</m> is the median
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            The mean is given by;
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow>\overline{\textbf{x}}  = \amp \frac{ \textbf{∑fx}}{ \textbf{∑f}} </mrow>
                                <mrow>=  \amp \frac{ 3,070,000}{ 50}</mrow>
                                <mrow>=  \amp 61,400</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            From the table;
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>\textbf{∑fx}</m> = <m>426.7</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>\textbf{∑f}</m> = <m>31</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow>=  \amp \frac{ 426.7}{ 31}</mrow>
                                <mrow>=  \amp 13.76</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The mean is, <m>13.76</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            
        </solution>
    </example>
